title: Neymar leads AP Global Football 10 after 4-goal game
text:
Home » News » Sports » Neymar leads AP Global… Neymar leads AP Global Football 10 after 4-goal game By JACK BEZANTS October 20, 2015 10:41 am FC Barcelona's Neymar, from Brazil, reacts after scoring against Rayo Vallecano during a Spanish La Liga soccer match at the Camp Nou stadium in Barcelona, Spain, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015. (AP Photo/Manu Fernandez) 
LONDON (AP) — Neymar took player of the week honors in The Associated Press Global Football 10 after scoring four goals in one game. 
The Brazil striker led the way as Barcelona beat Rayo Vallecano 5-2 on Saturday. 
Raheem Sterling was second after leading Manchester City to a 5-1 victory over Bournemouth with a first-half hat trick. Georginio Wijnaldum was third after also scoring four in Newcastle’s 6-2 win over Norwich, the team’s first win in the Premier League. 
Bayern Munich leads the team vote after winning its ninth straight match to start the Bundesliga season with a 1-0 victory at Werder Bremen. Manchester City is second after beating Bournemouth, while Barcelona is third. Topics:
